In the early 1980s almost everyone was extremely poor in China (over 90% of the population)

China's per capita income at the national level then was 1/3 that of Sub-Saharan Africa

Following years of stellar growth (averaging 10% real), extreme poverty in 2019 reached just 0.14%

Still, China's progress on extreme poverty reduction is real and remarkable

In merely 4 decades, the country managed to slash the number of extremely poor people from 910 million to 2 million

4/ https://t.co/5mMs3sYP6V

US poverty number is based on income, China's number on consumption

Big caveat: income-based measures are biased upwards (don't capture consumption smoothing from savings, subject to underreporting & other reasons)

So likely the real gap is smaller
